WEBVTT

00:03.422 --> 00:05.314
Okay munchkins, family meeting.

00:05.339 --> 00:06.791
Daddy and I have some exciting news.

00:06.816 --> 00:07.494
That's right.

00:07.519 --> 00:09.292
So, Katie, put your phone away. Emme,

00:09.317 --> 00:11.109
don't pick your nose. Teddy, buddy,

00:11.111 --> 00:12.544
stop touching yourself.

00:12.825 --> 00:13.578
I wasn't.

00:13.603 --> 00:14.886
You had both hands in your pants,

00:14.911 --> 00:17.412
moving around down there
like you're making origami.

00:18.989 --> 00:20.423
No hands in pants, all right?

00:20.425 --> 00:21.858
Let's make it a family motto.

00:22.575 --> 00:24.160
So, along with summer being over

00:24.162 --> 00:25.795
and school starting back up tomorrow,

00:25.797 --> 00:27.597
there's another change
happening in the family.

00:27.599 --> 00:30.233
I just got the official word and...

00:30.235 --> 00:31.868
I'm going back to work.

00:32.220 --> 00:33.183
Yay!

00:33.208 --> 00:35.215
- Yay!
- Yay!

00:35.240 --> 00:36.306
What's your job?

00:36.308 --> 00:37.507
It's the same job I had

00:37.509 --> 00:38.575
before you guys were born.

00:38.577 --> 00:39.676
I worked at a hospital,

00:39.678 --> 00:41.244
checking people's blood to find out

00:41.246 --> 00:42.545
what's making them sick.

00:42.547 --> 00:43.613
So you're a doctor?

00:43.615 --> 00:46.116
No.

00:46.118 --> 00:48.551
She's not a doctor.

00:48.553 --> 00:51.388
But it's very important work.

00:51.390 --> 00:53.809
Anyway, Daddy's gonna
be taking you to school,

00:53.834 --> 00:54.522
picking you up,

00:54.547 --> 00:56.169
watching you until I get
home, stuff like that.

00:56.194 --> 00:58.161
Yeah, since I'm a
contractor, I'm my own boss,

00:58.163 --> 01:00.697
so, I can work my
schedule around you guys.

01:00.699 --> 01:02.065
Look, all you guys need to know is,

01:02.067 --> 01:03.233
Daddy's in charge now.

01:03.235 --> 01:04.498
- That's right.
- Yeah!

01:04.524 --> 01:06.399
- Aw, bring it in.
- I love you, Daddy.

01:06.424 --> 01:08.191
Oh, you guys.

01:08.407 --> 01:10.040
We're gonna have so much fun.

01:10.042 --> 01:11.174
Can we get a puppy?

01:11.176 --> 01:12.375
- Sure.
- No!

01:12.377 --> 01:13.810
No...

01:13.812 --> 01:14.911
Well, which is it?

01:14.913 --> 01:17.213
Ask your mother. Not now.

01:17.215 --> 01:18.982
Do it later, when I'm not around.

01:20.419 --> 01:22.419
- Love you, Daddy.
- See?

01:22.421 --> 01:24.487
Katie thinks I'm doing great already.

01:24.489 --> 01:26.122
You can't trust a 13-year-old girl.

01:26.124 --> 01:28.091
She's all whacked out on hormones.

01:29.135 --> 01:30.093
Hormones?

01:30.095 --> 01:32.095
- Mm.
- My mom had those.

01:32.474 --> 01:33.468
She had to wear a patch

01:33.493 --> 01:35.993
just to keep from ripping our faces off.

01:36.970 --> 01:39.436
I can't believe I'm doing
this. I'm so excited.

01:40.006 --> 01:41.338
And guilty.

01:41.606 --> 01:43.273
And happy.

01:43.275 --> 01:44.974
And worried.

01:44.999 --> 01:46.450
You know, they make
a patch for that, too.

01:47.363 --> 01:48.302
Will you relax?

01:48.327 --> 01:49.662
Look, I got this.

01:49.664 --> 01:51.864
Me and the kids have a blast together.

01:51.866 --> 01:54.167
I'm Daddy fun times.

01:54.169 --> 01:55.457
Yeah, that's true.

01:55.482 --> 01:57.013
And I'll always be
home in time for dinner.

01:57.038 --> 01:58.338
- Yeah.
- I mean, it...

01:58.340 --> 02:00.173
it's not like I'm a doctor.

02:01.606 --> 02:02.842
Come on, honey,

02:02.844 --> 02:05.635
this was always the plan when
Emme started school full-time.

02:05.660 --> 02:06.612
Remember?

02:06.637 --> 02:08.705
Plus, we're gonna need the
extra money for college.

02:08.731 --> 02:10.389
Based on their ability
to flush a toilet,

02:10.414 --> 02:12.649
- I'm not seeing scholarships.
- You're right,

02:12.674 --> 02:15.121
it's fine because you are a great dad.

02:15.123 --> 02:16.422
- Oh...
- And it means so much to me,

02:16.447 --> 02:17.447
you stepping up like this.

02:17.472 --> 02:20.173
- Oh, well, I'm happy to do it.
- Mmm.

02:20.706 --> 02:22.405
And I'm not looking
for any kind of reward.

02:22.447 --> 02:23.396
Unless...

02:23.398 --> 02:25.036
you were thinking about
something, in which case,

02:25.061 --> 02:26.799
who am I to say no?

02:27.268 --> 02:28.935
Don't worry. You're
gonna get your reward.

02:29.663 --> 02:33.264
We're talking about
the same thing, right?

02:33.289 --> 02:35.156
You'll find out tonight.

02:37.541 --> 02:39.698
Okay, just one more picture.

02:39.723 --> 02:40.846
Oh, hey.

02:40.871 --> 02:44.350
Hold Emme in your arms sideways
like a big fish you just caught.

02:44.990 --> 02:46.519
Mom, we're not doing that.

02:46.750 --> 02:48.456
Okay, cut the cord and go to work.

02:48.481 --> 02:50.381
Yeah, I got to run.

02:50.688 --> 02:51.694
- Bye.
- I love you.

02:51.719 --> 02:53.052
- Love you, too.
- Love you.

02:53.077 --> 02:54.494
You, too.

02:55.112 --> 02:56.996
I am just so proud of you, sweet pea.

02:57.138 --> 02:59.705
You have a great first
day at school. Okay?

02:59.946 --> 03:01.244
Okay.

03:01.385 --> 03:02.584
Yeah...

03:06.162 --> 03:07.076
Daddy?

03:07.101 --> 03:08.107
Yeah, Butterbean?

03:08.109 --> 03:10.276
I'm worried about kindergarten.

03:10.481 --> 03:12.948
Aw, honey.

03:12.973 --> 03:14.906
You should be worried.

03:15.960 --> 03:18.451
Kids are mean.

03:18.453 --> 03:21.254
But just know if you
ever feel uncomfortable,

03:21.256 --> 03:22.522
you start swinging.

03:22.524 --> 03:23.723
Okay?

03:23.725 --> 03:24.620
A punch in the nose

03:24.645 --> 03:26.178
can be a real problem solver.

03:26.494 --> 03:28.828
Right? All right.

03:29.364 --> 03:30.732
Okay, bye, Daddy.

03:30.757 --> 03:32.390
Bye-bye, honey.

03:33.501 --> 03:35.368
Hello, kindergarten parents!

03:35.370 --> 03:38.383
I'm Mrs. Rodriguez, your
child's lead teacher.

03:38.408 --> 03:39.703
I'd like to welcome you all

03:39.728 --> 03:41.504
to the Kindergarten Parent Mingle.

03:41.971 --> 03:43.971
What?

03:43.996 --> 03:46.299
Now, has anyone seen Mrs. Burns?

03:46.301 --> 03:47.567
Is Mrs. Burns here?

03:47.569 --> 03:49.669
Uh, you must be talking about my wife.

03:49.671 --> 03:51.504
I'm Adam... uh, Mr. Burns.

03:51.506 --> 03:52.678
Oh, great.

03:52.703 --> 03:54.432
Mr. Burns, your wife
graciously volunteered

03:54.457 --> 03:56.522
to be our room parent, so
there's just a few things...

03:56.547 --> 03:57.243
Uh, listen,

03:57.245 --> 03:58.945
she's not gonna be able to do that.

03:58.947 --> 04:01.147
- See, she's decided to go back to work.
- Oh.

04:01.149 --> 04:02.710
Okay, so I'll just pencil you in.

04:02.735 --> 04:04.484
Whoa, hey, uh...

04:04.486 --> 04:05.635
I-I'd love to but, uh,

04:05.660 --> 04:06.998
I have a job, too, see,

04:07.023 --> 04:09.355
so please stop writing my name down.

04:09.357 --> 04:10.689
What a wonderful group,

04:10.714 --> 04:12.843
I can't wait to meet
each and every one of you!

04:12.868 --> 04:15.165
Mr. Burns, I'd like to
see you after the mingle.

04:18.064 --> 04:20.789
Hey, looks like you got
stuck in here too, huh?

04:20.791 --> 04:21.957
I'm Adam.

04:21.959 --> 04:22.809
Lowell.

04:22.834 --> 04:24.176
- I'm a stay-at-home dad.
- Oh.

04:24.201 --> 04:25.961
Four years now, it
hasn't changed me at all.

04:25.963 --> 04:27.162
Oh, you got a little something...

04:27.164 --> 04:28.931
Hey!

04:28.933 --> 04:30.766
I'm gonna say it has changed you.

04:31.192 --> 04:33.001
Sorry, I'm a little revved up.

04:33.003 --> 04:34.503
I just can't believe
they're not introducing

04:34.505 --> 04:36.271
any foreign language in kindergarten.

04:36.273 --> 04:37.706
How can our children compete

04:37.708 --> 04:40.809
in a global economy without
fluency in a second language?

04:43.948 --> 04:45.914
You know this school is free, right?

04:47.240 --> 04:49.184
Free stuff is not that great.

04:49.186 --> 04:50.686
Water is free,

04:50.688 --> 04:53.322
but beer you got to pay for. Hm?

04:53.833 --> 04:55.124
Beer.

04:55.531 --> 04:59.065
It's so great to connect
on a masculine level again.

05:04.969 --> 05:07.336
Where are the regular moms?

05:08.561 --> 05:09.507
Hey,

05:09.631 --> 05:10.832
I-I think I know you, right?

05:10.834 --> 05:13.476
Didn't you sneak a flask
into the school play?

05:13.501 --> 05:14.676
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

05:14.678 --> 05:15.744
Marie Faldanado.

05:15.746 --> 05:17.546
- Ah.
- My kid's in Teddy's class.

05:17.548 --> 05:19.119
Hey, uh, did Teddy get invited

05:19.144 --> 05:20.576
to Brady's birthday party?

05:20.601 --> 05:22.735
Because my Victor didn't
and it's happened before.

05:23.245 --> 05:24.891
Yeah, we had Victor
over last year, he's a...

05:24.916 --> 05:26.655
Oh, yeah, Victor.

05:26.657 --> 05:27.720
What?

05:27.745 --> 05:28.811
Well, he flushed a couple of

05:28.893 --> 05:30.460
Teddy's Hot Wheels down the toilet,

05:30.485 --> 05:31.415
he called my wife a hottie.

05:31.440 --> 05:33.295
He was kind of a jackass.

05:33.648 --> 05:37.383
I can't believe you'd
call my child that word!

05:38.710 --> 05:41.478
Hey-hey, isn't it two words?

05:44.287 --> 05:45.920
It's two words, right?

05:47.282 --> 05:50.556
And to make up for a
lack of funding, we depend

05:50.581 --> 05:51.972
on parent volunteers.

05:51.997 --> 05:53.148
I just think of the children.

05:53.150 --> 05:54.850
There's not a thing
I wouldn't do for them

05:54.852 --> 05:56.752
and I know you feel the same way.

05:57.310 --> 05:59.121
No.

05:59.508 --> 06:01.924
But everyone else has
refused to be room parent.

06:01.926 --> 06:04.526
Great, put me on that list.

06:05.295 --> 06:06.695
That's a shame.

06:07.343 --> 06:08.248
It would also be a shame if

06:08.273 --> 06:10.373
I don't teach your daughter to read.

06:12.203 --> 06:13.202
What are you saying?

06:13.204 --> 06:14.469
I said that's a shame.

06:14.471 --> 06:15.871
No, you said something after that.

06:15.873 --> 06:16.872
I don't think so.

06:16.874 --> 06:18.140
- Yes, you did...
- No, I didn't.

06:18.142 --> 06:19.074
- Yes, you did.
- No, I didn't.

06:19.076 --> 06:20.509
- Yes, you did...
- No, I didn't.

06:23.347 --> 06:24.680
- Yes, you did.
- Nope.

06:29.021 --> 06:30.285
Okay, I'll do it.

06:30.287 --> 06:31.653
Wonderful!

06:31.655 --> 06:33.121
Your first event is tomorrow's

06:33.123 --> 06:35.757
Ice Cream Sundae Fun
Day party at 11:00 a.m.

06:35.759 --> 06:36.873
Okay, but I mean,

06:36.898 --> 06:38.989
you're gonna teach Emme to read, right?

06:39.014 --> 06:41.181
We'll see how the party goes.

